### Problem Description

When changing the size of a ML nodes in a cloud deployment, the functionality to stop the deployment gracefully fails with a timeout when closing the pytorch process.

### Steps to Reproduce

1. Download and deploy ELSERv2 `.elser_model_2` with 2 assignments 1 thread each
2. Load the following commands into the dev console

<details><summary>Commands</summary>

```
PUT _snapshot/ml-data-snapshot-share
{
  "type": "gcs",
  "settings": {
    "bucket": "ml-data-snapshots-7-share",
    "client": "default"
  }
}

POST _snapshot/ml-data-snapshot-share/msmarco-datasets/_restore?wait_for_completion=false

PUT msmarco-passage-collection-elser
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "body": {
        "type": "text"
      },
      "ml": {
        "properties": {
          "tokens": {
            "type": "rank_features"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

# Ingest pipeline for ELSER
PUT _ingest/pipeline/elser
{
  "processors": [
    {
      "inference": {
        "model_id": ".elser_model_2",
        "field_map": {
          "body": "text_field"
        },
        "target_field": "ml",
        "inference_config": {
          "text_expansion": {
            "results_field": "tokens"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

PUT /_cluster/settings
{
  "transient": {
    "logger._root": "DEBUG"
  }
}

# ELSER-ise the MS MARCO passage collection with reindex
POST _reindex?wait_for_completion=false
{
  "source": {
    "index": "msmarco-passage-collection",
    "size": 100
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "msmarco-passage-collection-elser",
    "pipeline": "elser"
  }
}

GET _tasks/

```

</details>

